$ PowerShell: Unix and cmd.exe like aliases

→ Windows/PowerShell defines a few default → Windows/PowerShell/language/alias[aliases] that give → Linux[Linux] shell and former → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[cmd.exe] users a warm feeling:

table { ll

  ~Alias name~ ☰ ~aliased function~
  cat ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/content/get[Get-Content]
  cd ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location/set[Set-Location]
  chdir ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location/set[Set-Location]
  clear ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/host/clear[Clear-Host]
  copy ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/copy[Copy-Item]
  cp ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/copy[Copy-Item]
  del ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/remove[Remove-Item]
  diff ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/object/compare[Compare-Object]
  dir ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/childItem/get[Get-ChildItem]
  echo ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/output/write[Write-Output]
  erase ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/remove[Remove-Item]
  foreach ☰ ForEach-Object
  history ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/history/get[Get-History]
  kill ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/process/stop[Stop-Process]
  ls ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/childItem/get[Get-ChildItem]
  man ☰ help
  md ☰ mkdir
  mount ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/psDrive/new[New-PSDrive]
  move ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/move[Move-Item]
  mv ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/move[Move-Item]
  popd ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location/pop[Pop-Location]
  ps ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/process/get[Get-Process]
  pushd ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location/push[Push-Location]
  pwd ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/location/get[Get-Location]
  rm ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/remove[Remove-Item]
  rmdir ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/item/remove[Remove-Item]
  set ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/variable/set[Set-Variable]
  sleep ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/sleep/start[Start-Sleep]
  sort ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/object/sort[Sort-Object]
  tee ☰ Tee-Object
  type ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/content/get[Get-Content]
  where ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/object/where[Where-Object]
  write ☰ → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/output/write[Write-Output]

table }


sa:

  The → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic[automatic] variables → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/PID[`$PID`] and `$PWD` and
  the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference[preference] variable → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/preference/OFS[`$OFS`] also remind very much of Unix.

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/alias[alias]
